# Screen titles & descriptions

All **screen-level titles** and their **supporting descriptions** use shared type styles for consistency across home, setup, history, auth, and check-in.

## Title

- Use `Type.screenTitle` from `src/theme.ts` (`Slab.black` / Hepta Slab 900, `FontSize.display`, `letterSpacing: -1`).
- Do **not** use `Slab.bold` or `Slab.extraBold` for screen titles.
- Layer color, margin, and extra padding on top of `Type.screenTitle` as needed (e.g. mood `theme.ink`, descender padding on the home greeting).

## Description

- Use `Type.screenDescription` for the line under a screen title (auth tagline, setup blurb, history count, check-in prompt).
- Style: `Slab.bold`, `FontSize.lg`, `Colors.ink`.
- Layer margin only on top of `Type.screenDescription`.

Section labels and in-card habit titles are separate — these rules are for the primary page headline and its supporting line only.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — setup description out of sync with auth
description: {
  fontSize: FontSize.sm,
  fontFamily: Slab.regular,
  color: Colors.textSecondary,
}

// ✅ GOOD
import { Type } from '../src/theme';

greeting: {
  ...Type.screenTitle,
}

description: {
  ...Type.screenDescription,
  marginBottom: Spacing.lg,
}
```
